<br>
Everything was green except a few light blues.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Observations and concerns:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>1 -</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
The mobs have a TON of hit points and hit like pansies.<br>
<br>
This is possibly an indirect nerf to charming, since it won't be worth it really to turn these mobs against each other as the fights would take too long.<br>
<br>
After killing a bazillion mobs, I've noticed ZERO worthy drops. Not even anything useful to a level 35-50 player.<br>
<br>
Since I didn't get exp, I can only HOPE that for a level apropriate group, the exp is staggering and awesome here, because the loot is aweful.<br>
<br>
It takes so long to kill these, that I can't see it being worth Xp grinding here for anyone. I forsee this expansion being a ghost town in a month if they don't do something about that.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>2 -</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Pet aggro.<br>
<br>
I was roaming through with my level 65 Necromancer. I'd send my pet at a mob and the mob would completely ignore my pet and run at me while my pet beats on it HARD.<br>
<br>
I would usually feign it off, but often even when I stood up, the mob would turn on me again.<br>
<br>
In 65 Levels I've NEVER had a mob ignore my pet when I hadn't cast on it yet and I wasn't in melee range. (Except death touchers.)<br>
<br>
I decided to NOT feign once, and just kinda kited in circles checking to see what would happen with my Mage if I was there. (Granted, he's got Epic and if ANY beast in the game can get aggro it's him.)<br>
<br>
I kited around for a LONG time and it took a considerable time before it would turn on my pet, and I had to be very careful what I did or it would turn back on me.<br>
<br>
The Melee range was also HUGE on these and I had to get against the far wall quite often in the Mines of Torgiran to avoid being considered in &quot;Melee range&quot;<br>
<br>
Sit aggro was also monsterous as well.<br>
<br>
Very tough zones for something that's supposed to be for levels 35-60.<br>
<br>
Your thoughts and observations?<br>
<br>
