<br>
This is not an extension of PoP.  The title PoP implies one thing: mobs that hit obscenely hard but give obscene exp.  This is, IMO, one of _the_ biggest mistakes with the way PoP was designed in that it overpowered charm, made soloing extremely inefficient for any class who depends on fighting a monster blow-to-blow (all melees except rangers + shamans and mages), and made exping so easy that practically everyone's 65 in a couple of weeks and were AAxp farming.  <br>
<br>
Now, fast exp I don't mind, but fast exp while trivializing all other content?  That's the mistake PoP made - it became POINTLESS to exp anywhere BUT a PoP zone, because PoP exp was so obscenely fast.  This meant that any and every zone SoE made before POP is going to go down the toilet in the # of players / zone.  At the time, that was bad enough, but there is one more disadvantage that you don't consider when an expansion is first released:<br>
<br>
The fact that unless SOE makes ALL their future expansions like PoP in terms of exp-gain, PoP is going to be the exp expansion of choice for years to come.  In other words, every expansion post-PoP must have PoP's exp modifier or become ghost towns and underused.<br>
<br>
This fact has come back to bite SoE in the ass.  Right now, people are still in LoY in troves because they're searching for charms and possible good drops, but once these farm-fests end, LoY is going to become a ghost town just like Cazic Thule, Sebilils, and Chardok are nowadays.  Those zones used to be hot - _the_ exp zones of choice where the risk was high but the rewards were higher.  Now they're empty.  Why? Because you can exp in PoP instead, where the risk is really not fainting because of boredom (let's face it, how hard is it to fight golems in PoValor? Yet that's one of the best exp spots in the game) and the rewards are many times that of other zones in terms of exp.<br>
<br>
It's not LOY's fault, really, that people will come to neglect it.  LoY is a very balanced expansion - the mobs aren't particularly hard (I don't know what problems you were having, personally, but 170-200 hitting mobs with 10-15k hps is about right for the levels/loots these guys drop.  Look at CT - the mobs there hit for 220-400, but their levels are similar to those of LoY mobs.)  and there are good loots to be found in every zone - plus each zone is pretty interesting in its own respect and can all be considered fun dungeon crawls.  <br>
<br>
If there's any expansion to blame in the days to come, it should be PoP.<br>
