<br>
What is the net effect of high regeneration mobs?<br>
<br>
First, it lowers the value of slow.  Making the fight longer means more time to regeneration.<br>
<br>
Second, it exaggerates the difference between mediocre and high damage dealers.   You essentially subtract the regeneration rate from the group DPS, which means low DPS essentially stands still.  At the same time, high hitpoints also reduces the relative value of damage dealing itself.  It negates group power.<br>
<br>
Third, it makes soloing less valuable, and larger high DPS groups more valuable.  You need to deal enough damage to counter the regeneration <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">and</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> kill the mob in a reasonable amount of time.<br>
<br>
If balanced correctly, it would work in the favor of high DPS melees, since the fights are longer and sustained DPS becomes more important.  However, I doubt it, simply because <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Verant</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> appears to rarely correctly foresee the consequences of their choices.  Caster DPS is so much higher than melee DPS nowadays that I doubt the fights will last long enough for the sustainability of melee damage to win through.<br>
<br>
While it would encourage full groups, only the most effective damage dealers will be welcome beyond the core of the group.  Mediocre classes would be even more marginalized.<br>
